We've already disabled it, Mr. Mayor.

21
00:02:00,849 --> 00:02:02,515
你的筆記本電腦和手機也是
Same with your laptop and cell.

22
00:02:02,517 --> 00:02:04,417
你們確定沒問題了嗎 因為
Yeah. You sure about that? 'Cause, uh,

23
00:02:04,419 --> 00:02:06,620
我不想再有什麼漏洞 我的麻煩已經夠多了
I don't need no more leaks. I got enough problems.

24
00:02:06,622 --> 00:02:08,855
要知道 有些人不遺餘力地
Certain people try to bring me down

25
00:02:08,857 --> 00:02:11,157
想扳倒我
any way they can, you know?

26
00:02:11,159 --> 00:02:13,827
我們接下來會檢查您的車子和家裏
We'll scan your car and home next.

27
00:02:13,829 --> 00:02:16,196
目前為止 這個房間是安全的
But, for now, this room's secure.

28
00:02:16,198 --> 00:02:18,365
好的 電話也安全嗎
Good. Phones, too?

29
00:02:18,367 --> 00:02:19,733
呃 別用座機
Uh, don't use landlines.

30
00:02:19,735 --> 00:02:21,468
但如果你的助理發現 聽筒裏有回音或敲擊聲
But make sure your assistant lets you know

31
00:02:21,470 --> 00:02:22,969
讓她一定要告訴你
if she hears any echoes or clicks.

32
00:02:22,971 --> 00:02:24,471
有可能是線路竊聽
Could mean a wiretap.

33
00:02:24,473 --> 00:02:26,506
如果真的是竊聽 我們應該可以追查到源頭
And, if so, we should be able to trace its source.

34
00:02:26,508 --> 00:02:27,874
手機呢 沒問題嗎
What about cell phones-- they good?

35
00:02:27,876 --> 00:02:29,242
手機沒問題
Cell's good.

36
00:02:29,244 --> 00:02:32,412
好的 那我們也沒問題了
All right. We're good, then.

37
00:02:32,414 --> 00:02:33,880
兩千 是嗎
2,000, right?

38
00:02:33,882 --> 00:02:35,615
不必了 我們會給你寄賬單
Uh, that's okay, we'll just bill you.

39
00:02:35,617 --> 00:02:37,050
不 不行
Uh, no. No, no.

40
00:02:37,052 --> 00:02:38,451
不要賬單
No bills.

41
00:02:38,453 --> 00:02:40,553
這事只有你我知道 明白嗎
It's between us, you understand?

42
00:02:40,555 --> 00:02:41,755
明白了
Understood.

43
00:02:41,757 --> 00:02:43,690
好的
Okay.

44
00:02:49,264 --> 00:02:51,331
-你好 -Frank 我是Hamilton
- Hello? - Frank, it's Hamilton.

45
00:02:51,333 --> 00:02:53,066
你確定這條線沒問題嗎
Are you sure this line is secure?

46
00:02:53,068 --> 00:02:54,768
說實話 我現在對什麼都不確定了
Honestly, I'm not sure about anything anymore.

47
00:02:54,770 --> 00:02:56,469
讓我非常困擾
Gotten in pretty deep here.

48
00:02:56,471 --> 00:02:58,905
你也不該感到確定 市長先生 因為我
Nor should you be, Mr. Mayor, 'cause I'm gonna be

49
00:02:58,907 --> 00:03:00,840
就站在你跟前 寶貝兒
up and in your grill, baby.

50
00:03:00,842 --> 00:03:03,977
他都清理過手機了 我們怎麼還能竊聽他
How can we still hear him if they swept his cell?

51
00:03:03,979 --> 00:03:07,447
你是無法清理3P的影子應用的
You can't sweep a Triple P shadow app,

52
00:03:07,449 --> 00:03:09,983
這個應用讓我能竊聽並錄下
which allows me to listen to and record

53
00:03:09,985 --> 00:03:12,953
聽得見的任何聲音
any and everything within earshot.

54
00:03:12,955 --> 00:03:15,055
問題在於 不是所有事情
Problem is, anything and everything isn't covered

55
00:03:15,057 --> 00:03:16,690
都在竊聽令的許可範圍
under the wiretap warrant.

56
00:03:16,692 --> 00:03:18,491
只能是關於清水市
Only what's related to Clearwater

57
00:03:18,493 --> 00:03:20,727
或者他所謂的海外行賄基金
or his alleged offshore slush funds.

58
00:03:20,729 --> 00:03:22,062
還有Javier Garcia的謀殺案
And Javier Garcia's murder.

59
00:03:22,064 --> 00:03:23,530
告訴Jess
Let Jess know,

60
00:03:23,532 --> 00:03:26,066
我這段時間不能見她了
uh, I won't be seeing her for a while.

61
00:03:26,068 --> 00:03:28,868
不能冒險讓媒體再挖出什麼緋聞了
Can't risk the media finding out about any more of these affairs.

62
00:03:28,870 --> 00:03:31,705
-停止錄音 -等等 什麼
- Stop recording. - Wait, what?

63
00:03:31,707 --> 00:03:33,239
私人信息
Personal information is not covered

64
00:03:33,241 --> 00:03:35,075
不在竊聽範圍之內
under the scope of the wiretap.

65
00:03:35,077 --> 00:03:37,744
聽著 Dwayne 如果不能嚴格按照要求執行
Look, Dwayne, if this isn't done within the strict parameters

66
00:03:37,746 --> 00:03:39,813
在法庭上是站不住腳的
of the order, it won't stand up in court.

67
00:03:39,815 --> 00:03:42,048
市長並不乾淨 Karen
Mayor's dirty, Karen.

68
00:03:42,050 --> 00:03:44,484
Rita讓這個案子正式成立了
Look, Rita's put together a solid circumstantial case,

69
00:03:44,486 --> 00:03:47,153
但是Jenkins... 他是唯一一個願意
but Jenkins-- he was the only judge willing to risk

70
00:03:47,155 --> 00:03:50,156
冒險跟Hamilton對立 同意竊聽的法官
going up against Hamilton to grant the tap.

71
00:03:50,158 --> 00:03:52,158
我知道你們有多想扳倒他
I know how bad you want to take him down,

72
00:03:52,160 --> 00:03:53,994
但如果你們不按法律條文辦事
but if you don't do this by the book,

73
00:03:53,996 --> 00:03:55,362
你們會失去竊聽許可
you're gonna blow the wiretap.

74
00:03:55,364 --> 00:03:57,630
Hamilton就會從謀殺案脫身
And Hamilton gets away with murder.

75
00:03:57,632 --> 00:03:59,666
還有其它案件
And everything else.

76
00:04:01,470 --> 00:04:03,136
停止錄音
Stop recording.

77
00:04:06,108 --> 00:04:08,174
好了 我有案子了
Ah, all right, I got a case.

78
00:04:08,176 --> 00:04:09,843
繼續監視市長
Keep monitoring the mayor.

79
00:04:09,845 --> 00:04:12,479
你確定Patton知道監聽的關鍵字嗎
Are you sure Patton knows what keywords to listen for?

80
00:04:12,481 --> 00:04:13,980
他知道清水市案子的
Is he read in on Clearwater,

81
00:04:13,982 --> 00:04:15,482
全部細節了嗎
every detail?

82
00:04:15,484 --> 00:04:17,350
不 不是全部
No, not everything.

83
00:04:17,352 --> 00:04:19,786
那我要是你 我會待在這裏
Then I'd stay put if I were you.

84
00:04:19,788 --> 00:04:22,155
拿下Hamilton可能只有這一次機會
May only get this one shot at Hamilton.

85
00:04:32,134 --> 00:04:35,035
Pride還好嗎 他聽起來怎麼樣
Yeah, is Pride all right? How'd he sound?

86
00:04:35,037 --> 00:04:36,569
糾結
Torn.

87
00:04:36,571 --> 00:04:38,004
必須說服他待在那裏
Had to talk him into staying put,

88
00:04:38,006 --> 00:04:39,339
集中精力扳倒Hamilton
focusing on trying to get Hamilton

89
00:04:39,341 --> 00:04:40,640
在他幹掉我們之前
before Hamilton gets us.

90
00:04:40,642 --> 00:04:42,442
是啊 King對工作很忠誠
Yeah, King's loyal to the job.

91
00:04:42,444 --> 00:04:45,345
讓他放棄主導案件偵破很不容易
It's not easy for him not taking the lead on a case.

92
00:04:45,347 --> 00:04:47,147
所以我們更要把這個案子辦得漂漂亮亮
All the more reason for us to kick ass on this one.

93
00:04:47,149 --> 00:04:48,615
你要我去接Percy嗎
Do you want me to go pick up Percy?

94
00:04:48,617 --> 00:04:51,117
不用 我已經在咖啡店這裏了
No, I'm already here at the coffee shop.

95
00:04:51,119 --> 00:04:53,086
我們一會兒在犯罪...
We'll meet you at the crime...

96
00:04:54,122 --> 00:04:56,089
現場見
...scene.

97
00:04:57,826 --> 00:04:59,859
Lasalle
Lasalle?

98
00:05:01,129 --> 00:05:02,796
Lasalle 你還在嗎
Lasalle, you still there?

99
00:05:02,798 --> 00:05:05,065
是 我還在
Yeah, I'm still here.

100
00:05:05,067 --> 00:05:06,633
一會見
We'll see you in a bit.

101
00:05:06,635 --> 00:05:08,535
嗨
Hey!

102
00:05:08,537 --> 00:05:10,036
鄉下鼠
Country Mouse.

103
00:05:10,038 --> 00:05:11,504
早知道是你來接我
If I knew you were my ride,

104
00:05:11,506 --> 00:05:13,440
我會給你帶個羊角麵包
I would've picked you up a croissant.

105
00:05:16,645 --> 00:05:17,677
一切還好嗎
Everything all right?

106
00:05:17,679 --> 00:05:20,747
當然 我們出發吧
Yeah, sure. Let's roll.

107
00:05:33,061 --> 00:05:34,961
嘿 你確定沒什麼心事嗎
Hey, you sure nothing's bothering you?

108
00:05:34,963 --> 00:05:36,796
我嗎 沒啊 怎麼了
Me? No, why?

109
00:05:36,798 --> 00:05:38,498
我不知道 也許是因為這一路上
I don't know, maybe 'cause you only said, like,

110
00:05:38,500 --> 00:05:40,533
你只跟我說了兩個字
two words to me on the way over.

111
00:05:40,535 --> 00:05:42,268
是我哎 怎麼回事
Come on, it's me. What?

112
00:05:42,270 --> 00:05:43,603
Gregorio 我們掌握了什麼
Gregorio, what do we got?

113
00:05:43,605 --> 00:05:44,938
你也好啊 Christopher
Hello to you, too, Christopher.

114
00:05:44,940 --> 00:05:46,573
哦 姐們兒 他心情不太好
Oh, girl, he is in a mood.

115
00:05:46,575 --> 00:05:48,541
看得出來
I can see that.

116
00:05:48,543 --> 00:05:50,043
搶劫團伙很專業
Heist crew were pros,

117
00:05:50,045 --> 00:05:51,845
幹掉了監控 阻斷了通訊
took out cameras, jammed communication,

118
00:05:51,847 --> 00:05:54,114
很清楚地知道他們想要的東西是什麼 在哪裏
knew exactly what they were after and where to get it.

119
00:05:54,116 --> 00:05:55,849
Sebastian 貨物是什麼
Sebastian, what's the haul?

120
00:05:55,851 --> 00:05:57,884
運往Fort Bragg基地的幾百個MP5衝鋒鎗
Couple hundred MP5s headed to Fort Bragg.

121
00:05:57,886 --> 00:05:59,519
海軍還在清查庫存
The Navy's still doing an inventory

122
00:05:59,521 --> 00:06:01,187
以獲知準確數目 不過...
to get an exact count, but...

123
00:06:01,189 --> 00:06:03,656
那可是大批量的重火力武器
That's a lot of serious firepower.

124
00:06:03,658 --> 00:06:05,892
我是說 這不可能只是為了
I mean, this can't just be about selling them

125
00:06:05,894 --> 00:06:07,360
到黑市上去賣吧
on the black market.

126
00:06:07,362 --> 00:06:09,062
我們遇到了民兵組織之類的嗎
We're dealing with some kind of militia?

127
00:06:09,064 --> 00:06:11,064
不管他們是誰 都是有備而來的
Well, whoever it was, they came prepared.

128
00:06:11,066 --> 00:06:13,867
根據鐵路警察的說法 他們都有防彈衣
According to the railway cops, they all had body armor,

129
00:06:13,869 --> 00:06:15,969
用的是AR-15突擊步槍 震盪手雷
were using AR-15s, concussive grenades.

130
00:06:15,971 --> 00:06:17,337
有多少人受傷
How many were injured?

131
00:06:17,339 --> 00:06:18,571
怪就怪在這兒 沒人受傷
That's the thing-- none.

132
00:06:18,573 --> 00:06:22,475
哇 搶劫團伙用了AR-15突擊步槍 手雷
Whoa. Heist crew using AR-15s, grenades,

133
00:06:22,477 --> 00:06:26,045
帶著MP5衝鋒鎗逃跑 竟然沒一個警察中槍
making off with MP5s, and no cop gets shot?

134
00:06:26,047 --> 00:06:28,381
不 警察們被射擊了 但射中他們的不是子彈
Oh, no, cops were shot all right, just not with bullets.

135
00:06:28,383 --> 00:06:29,749
沒錯 不是致命的子彈
Yeah, not with lethal rounds.

136
00:06:29,751 --> 00:06:31,117
而是橡膠子彈
With rubber bullets.

137
00:06:31,119 --> 00:06:32,352
專門設計的複合材料
Specifically designed composite,

138
00:06:32,354 --> 00:06:33,686
就像中了一記重拳一樣
packs a heck of a punch,

139
00:06:33,688 --> 00:06:35,221
尤其是用AR-15射出來
especially coming out of an AR-15.

140
00:06:35,223 --> 00:06:37,190
能打得你喘不過氣來
It's more than enough to knock the wind out of you.

141
00:06:37,192 --> 00:06:39,259
-但不會死人 -那麼問題來了
- But not kill. - Which begs the question,

142
00:06:39,261 --> 00:06:41,461
什麼樣的搶劫團伙 去偷上百個致命武器
what kind of heist crew steals hundreds of lethal weapons

143
00:06:41,463 --> 00:06:43,129
會帶非致命武器呢
using nonlethal rounds?

144
00:06:43,131 --> 00:06:44,531
是啊 這說不通
Yeah. Doesn't make sense.

145
00:06:44,533 --> 00:06:45,899
是的 但幸虧鐵路警察
Yeah, well, fortunately the rail cops

146
00:06:45,901 --> 00:06:47,534
用的是真子彈
were using live ammo.

147
00:06:49,237 --> 00:06:50,570
他們打中了一個團伙成員
They tagged one of the crew.

148
00:06:50,572 --> 00:06:53,173
流了不少血 我應該能通過DNA查明身份
Lost a lot of blood. I should be able to get a DNA I.D.

149
00:06:53,175 --> 00:06:54,908
好的 有發現就告訴我們 Sebastian
All right, let us know what you find, Sebastian.

150
00:06:54,910 --> 00:06:56,976
那個有錢人是誰
Who's the fat cat?

151
00:06:57,946 --> 00:06:59,946
槍支製造公司的老闆
Owner of the company that makes the guns,

152
00:06:59,948 --> 00:07:01,181
Justus Bancroft
Justus Bancroft.

153
00:07:01,183 --> 00:07:02,715
或者說是受害者
Or the victim.

154
00:07:02,717 --> 00:07:05,418
慢著 在ATF裏待了那麼多年
Whoa. Spent a lot of years at ATF

155
00:07:02,717 --> 00:07:05,418
{\a6}煙酒、火器與爆炸物管理局

156
00:07:05,420 --> 00:07:07,987
看過Bancroft的槍械產品所造成的傷害
seeing the pain Bancroft guns cause.

157
00:07:07,989 --> 00:07:10,190
很難把他們當成受害人
Hardly makes them a victim.

158
00:07:12,360 --> 00:07:13,626
打擾一下
Excuse me.

159
00:07:13,628 --> 00:07:16,863
海軍罪案調查處 可以和我聊聊嗎
NCIS. Mind if I get a word?

160
00:07:16,865 --> 00:07:19,032
不好意思 請問有什麼問題嗎
Sorry, is there a problem?

161
00:07:19,034 --> 00:07:21,134
不 當然沒問題
No, no, no, not at all.

162
00:07:21,136 --> 00:07:22,635
只是 呃
It's just that, uh, well,

163
00:07:22,637 --> 00:07:24,604
我們已經把知道的都告訴警察了
we already told the police everything we know.

164
00:07:24,606 --> 00:07:26,139
而且我們必須走了
And we have to go.

165
00:07:26,141 --> 00:07:28,374
抱歉 請問你是
I'm sorry, who are you?

166
00:07:28,376 --> 00:07:29,809
Nadine
Nadine.

167
00:07:29,811 --> 00:07:31,244
Bancroft
Bancroft.

168
00:07:32,547 --> 00:07:35,148
特別探員Lasalle
Special Agent Lasalle.

169
00:07:35,150 --> 00:07:37,483
我們之後會和警方溝通 但如果你不介意的話...
We'll talk with NOPD afterwards, but if you don't mind...

170
00:07:37,485 --> 00:07:41,120
當然不介意 儘管問
No, no, of course, of course. Ask me anything.

171
00:07:41,122 --> 00:07:43,156
只不過 呃 我們明天
Well, it's just that, uh, we're hosting

172
00:07:43,158 --> 00:07:44,958
要舉辦年度慈善活動
our annual charity event tomorrow.

173
00:07:44,960 --> 00:07:48,761
我倒是覺得幾百支衝鋒鎗不知所蹤
I kind of think a couple hundred missing submachine guns

174
00:07:48,763 --> 00:07:50,964
比你們的小派對更重要 不是嗎
trumps your little party, don't you?

175
00:07:50,966 --> 00:07:52,065
Percy
Percy.

176
00:07:53,001 --> 00:07:54,901
無意冒犯 但是
No disrespect, but, uh,

177
00:07:54,903 --> 00:07:57,470
我們的工作還是要做的 而且槍支數量很多
we got to do our jobs, and that's a lot of guns.

178
00:07:57,472 --> 00:07:59,072
對 相信我 我理解
Oh, yeah, trust me, I know.

179
00:07:59,074 --> 00:08:01,040
這也不是我們第一次遭遇這種事了
It's not the first time we've been hit, either.

180
00:08:01,042 --> 00:08:02,275
你們以前也被搶劫過
You've been robbed before?

181
00:08:02,277 --> 00:08:04,911
沒有這麼嚴重 但是有過
Well, not to this extent, but yes.

182
00:08:04,913 --> 00:08:06,980
FBI ATF 他們都
Uh, the FBI, ATF, they both investigated

183
00:08:06,982 --> 00:08:09,349
調查過前兩次搶劫 但無功而返
the other two times, and, uh, come up empty.

184
00:08:09,351 --> 00:08:11,784
我很高興沒有警察受傷
I'm just glad none of the police got hurt.

185
00:08:11,786 --> 00:08:14,520
三次 這裏面一定有什麼聯繫
Well, third time, there's got to be a connection.

186
00:08:14,522 --> 00:08:16,823
我們會深入調查 並通知你我們的進展
We'll dig into it and let you know what we find.

187
00:08:16,825 --> 00:08:18,424
-好的 -我們會和你保持聯繫
- All right. - We'll be in touch.

188
00:08:18,426 --> 00:08:20,493
你隨時可以聯繫我
You, uh, call me anytime.

189
00:08:20,495 --> 00:08:22,128
-謝謝 -好了
- Thank you. - All right.

190
00:08:22,130 --> 00:08:23,263
謝謝
Thanks.

191
00:08:25,166 --> 00:08:27,500
我覺得King
I don't think King

192
00:08:27,502 --> 00:08:29,736
不會喜歡你對她說話的態度
would've much liked the way you talked to her.

193
00:08:29,738 --> 00:08:32,238
我還不喜歡你對我說話的態度呢
Don't much like the way you talked to me.

194
00:08:32,240 --> 00:08:33,840
她的反應就好像這一切
She acted like this was nothing more

195
00:08:33,842 --> 00:08:36,209
只是些麻煩而已
than an inconvenience.

196
00:08:36,211 --> 00:08:37,944
你不覺得奇怪嗎
That didn't bother you?

197
00:08:37,946 --> 00:08:39,979
哦 我忘了
Oh, I forgot,

198
00:08:39,981 --> 00:08:42,682
你對什麼都無所謂
nothing's bothering you.

199
00:08:42,684 --> 00:08:44,117
對吧
Right.

200
00:08:49,691 --> 00:08:51,057
在我的辦公桌上工作還自在嗎
Making yourself at home at my desk?

201
00:08:51,059 --> 00:08:52,659
哦 Pride 不 不 抱歉
Oh, Pride, no, no, no. I'm sorry.

202
00:08:52,661 --> 00:08:53,960
我就是 我不想
I just, I didn't want to

203
00:08:53,962 --> 00:08:55,628
-打擾你和Patton -沒事 Sebastian
- bother you and Patton. - It's okay, Sebastian.

204
00:08:55,630 --> 00:08:57,196
開個玩笑 坐吧
Just teasing. Sit down.

205
00:08:57,198 --> 00:09:00,566
能和你換位置再高興不過了 真的
Be more than happy to trade places with you, believe me.

206
00:09:00,568 --> 00:09:02,502
坐在竊聽設備旁有點兒無聊吧
Sitting on a wiretap's kind of boring, huh?

207
00:09:02,504 --> 00:09:03,770
不如說是單調乏味
More like tedious.

208
00:09:03,772 --> 00:09:05,438
而且 我知道了越來越多
Plus, I'm learning more about Hamilton

209
00:09:05,440 --> 00:09:07,907
壓根不想知道的Hamilton的事 太多了
than I ever wanted to know. A lot more.

210
00:09:07,909 --> 00:09:10,943
但沒能把他和謀殺案或清水市聯繫起來嗎
But nothing that connects him to the murders or Clearwater?

211
00:09:10,945 --> 00:09:12,612
還沒有
Not yet.

212
00:09:12,614 --> 00:09:13,613
但這只是
But it's just

213
00:09:13,615 --> 00:09:14,881
時間問題
a matter of time.

214
00:09:14,883 --> 00:09:16,482
案子進展怎麼樣了
Where are you on the case?

215
00:09:16,484 --> 00:09:19,152
用我在犯罪現場找到的DNA
Well, using the DNA I found at the crime scene,

216
00:09:19,154 --> 00:09:21,087
我嘗試確認傷者的身份
I'm trying to I.D. our wounded bad guy,

217
00:09:21,089 --> 00:09:22,255
但迄今為止 一無所獲
but nothing's coming up so far,

218
00:09:22,257 --> 00:09:23,790
這個 有點兒奇怪
which is, you know, a little odd.

219
00:09:23,792 --> 00:09:25,558
好的 但並非異常
Okay. But not unusual.

220
00:09:25,560 --> 00:09:26,993
我剛和FBI打完電話
I just got off the phone with FBI,

221
00:09:26,995 --> 00:09:28,928
看了之前的搶劫記錄 他們也沒有任何發現
checked on the prior heists, and they got nothing, either.

222
00:09:28,930 --> 00:09:30,730
難以置信
Well, that's hard to believe.

223
00:09:30,732 --> 00:09:32,632
三起搶劫大案 沒有一點證據
Three high-profile hits, no evidence.

224
00:09:32,634 --> 00:09:33,933
這怎麼可能呢
How's that possible?

225
00:09:33,935 --> 00:09:35,401
更奇怪的是 以前被偷的槍
Even stranger, none of the past stolen guns

226
00:09:35,403 --> 00:09:37,003
沒有一支出現在街頭或者黑市
have showed up on the street or black market.

227
00:09:37,005 --> 00:09:38,237
它們就像消失了一樣
It's as if they just disappeared.

228
00:09:38,239 --> 00:09:41,240
也許我該和你們一起調查的
Yeah, maybe I should get involved.

229
00:09:41,242 --> 00:09:42,508
不行 Hamilton知道你在查他
No, Hamilton knows you're after him.

230
00:09:42,510 --> 00:09:43,910
你現在不能鬆懈 這太重要了
You can't let up now. It's too important.

231
00:09:43,912 --> 00:09:45,878
幾百支失蹤的槍也很重要
So is a couple hundred missing guns.

232
00:09:45,880 --> 00:09:47,880
哦 怪不得我一直匹配不上
Oh, no wonder I didn't get a match.

233
00:09:47,882 --> 00:09:51,184
我把查找的罪犯性別設置成了男性 而不是女性
I programmed the I.D. search for bad guys, not bad girls.

234
00:09:51,186 --> 00:09:52,118
這是性別歧視 順便說一下
That's male bias, by the way.

235
00:09:52,120 --> 00:09:53,486
我為此道歉
I apologize for that.

236
00:09:53,488 --> 00:09:55,955
Josephine Bellacroix
Uh, Josephine Bellacroix.

237
00:09:55,957 --> 00:09:57,290
中尉 新奧爾良出生
First Lieutenant, born in New Orleans.

238
00:09:57,292 --> 00:09:58,358
海軍陸戰隊員嗎
A Marine?

239
00:09:58,360 --> 00:09:59,726
對 而且檔案非常乾淨
Yeah, flawless record, too.

240
00:09:59,728 --> 00:10:02,762
她去過索馬裏和蘇丹
She did a tour in Somalia and Sudan.

241
00:10:02,764 --> 00:10:04,297
一年前離開了軍隊
Left the Corps a year ago.

242
00:10:04,299 --> 00:10:06,466
剛好在第一次劫案發生前
Just before the first heist.

243
00:10:06,468 --> 00:10:08,501
不知道是什麼讓她開始偷槍的
Wonder what made her start stealing guns.

244
00:10:08,503 --> 00:10:10,403
帶她回來 查清楚
Pick her up, find out.

245
00:10:10,405 --> 00:10:11,738
-在你去之前... -好的 我先給Lasalle打電話
- And before you do that... - All right, I'll call Lasalle.

246
00:10:11,740 --> 00:10:13,172
他和Sonja還在值外勤
He and Sonja are still in the field.

247
00:10:13,174 --> 00:10:15,341
Sebastian 著手調查她的同事
Sebastian, start looking for known associates,

248
00:10:15,343 --> 00:10:16,511
看能不能找到她的同夥
see if we can find out who she's working with.

249
00:10:16,535 --> 00:10:17,611
這就查
I'm on it.

250
00:10:17,612 --> 00:10:19,045
嘿
Hey.

251
00:10:19,848 --> 00:10:21,814
我們可以的 不要擔心
We got this. Don't worry about us.

252
00:10:33,161 --> 00:10:35,161
如果你一直對我採取沉默的方式
If you're gonna keep giving me the silent treatment

253
00:10:35,163 --> 00:10:36,629
來折磨我
and being mean to me...

254
00:10:36,631 --> 00:10:38,097
我沒折磨你
I'm not being mean to you.

255
00:10:38,099 --> 00:10:40,566
好吧 那是怎麼回事
Okay, so what's your problem?

256
00:10:40,568 --> 00:10:42,802
我不明白
I don't understand.

257
00:10:42,804 --> 00:10:45,004
我就是對今早的事情很吃驚
I was just surprised this morning,

258
00:10:45,006 --> 00:10:47,673
看到你和那個人在咖啡館
seeing you with that guy at the coffee shop.

259
00:10:47,675 --> 00:10:50,343
等等 Tom嗎
Wait, Tom?

260
00:10:50,345 --> 00:10:52,245
我不知道你在跟人約會
I didn't know you were dating anybody.

261
00:10:52,247 --> 00:10:54,647
我沒在約會
I'm not dating anybody.

262
00:10:54,649 --> 00:10:56,082
只是喝咖啡而已
It was just coffee.

263
00:10:56,084 --> 00:10:57,784
再說 我一點都不瞭解他
Besides, I barely know that guy.

264
00:10:57,786 --> 00:10:59,819
你已經瞭解到可以親他了
Well, you knew him well enough to kiss him.

265
00:10:59,821 --> 00:11:02,422
我沒親他 是他親的我
I didn't kiss-- he kissed me.

266
00:11:05,593 --> 00:11:06,993
你是在吃醋嗎
Are you jealous?

267
00:11:06,995 --> 00:11:08,694
吃醋
Jealous.

268
00:11:08,696 --> 00:11:10,663
-你吃醋了 -你發什麼瘋呢
- You're jealous. - You're trippin' girl.

269
00:11:10,665 --> 00:11:13,099
快點 準備武器
Come on. Let's gear up.

270
00:11:25,847 --> 00:11:28,114
散彈鎗 不是吧
Shotguns? Really?

271
00:11:28,116 --> 00:11:29,715
受傷的陸戰隊員
Yeah, wounded Marine.

272
00:11:29,717 --> 00:11:32,418
她手裏應該有一把MP5衝鋒鎗
She's probably armed with a MP5 by now.

273
00:11:32,420 --> 00:11:34,187
還是小心點好
Better safe than sorry.

274
00:11:37,225 --> 00:11:39,225
聯邦探員
Federal agents!

275
00:11:44,199 --> 00:11:45,898
Percy
Percy.

276
00:11:52,907 --> 00:11:55,808
這不可能只是搶劫中的槍
No way that's just from the heist shooting.

277
00:12:05,193 --> 00:12:07,393
街對面的房子裝有安全監控
House across the street has a security camera,

278
00:12:07,395 --> 00:12:09,161
但攝像頭的角度難以確定
but it's a bad angle to I.D. anyone

279
00:12:09,163 --> 00:12:11,197
進出Bellacroix房子的人的身份
going in and out of Bellacroix's place.

280
00:12:11,199 --> 00:12:14,233
所以沒人拿著MP5衝鋒鎗走出來嗎
Ooh, so no one walking out with an MP5?

281
00:12:14,235 --> 00:12:16,435
有個拿著小包的女士 就這樣
Lady carrying a small bag. That's about it.

282
00:12:16,437 --> 00:12:17,703
這看起來越來越像
It's looking more and more like

283
00:12:17,705 --> 00:12:19,605
那個團伙為了掩蓋蹤跡幹掉了她
the crew took her out to cover their tracks.

284
00:12:19,607 --> 00:12:22,542
找個兇狠的傢伙把自己人幹掉
Takes a pretty vicious crew to take out one of their own.

285
00:12:22,544 --> 00:12:23,809
我們得查出他們是誰
We need to find out who they are

286
00:12:23,811 --> 00:12:25,811
這樣才能盡快找回那些槍
so we can get those guns back, fast.

287
00:12:25,813 --> 00:12:28,114
問題是 他們在掩蓋行蹤上做得太好了
The problem is, they're so good at covering their tracks,

288
00:12:28,116 --> 00:12:29,582
我們什麼都沒查到
we got squat.

289
00:12:29,584 --> 00:12:33,052
要是我們能查清楚 一開始是什麼讓一個光榮的陸戰隊員
Yeah. If we could just figure out what made a decorated Marine

290
00:12:33,054 --> 00:12:35,121
加入一個搶劫團伙
join a heist crew in the first place.

291
00:12:35,123 --> 00:12:37,123
你確定在她的服役記錄中
Are you sure there weren't any red flags

292
00:12:37,125 --> 00:12:38,324
沒有任何危險信號嗎
in her service record?

293
00:12:38,326 --> 00:12:40,359
沒有創傷後應激障礙 沒有心理恐慌
No PTSD, no psych alarm.

294
00:12:40,361 --> 00:12:43,262
她的同事中是否有犯罪記錄
Any of her known associates with criminal backgrounds?

295
00:12:43,264 --> 00:12:44,699
沒有 Bellacroix是新奧爾良本地人
No. Bellacroix's a NOLA native,

296
00:12:44,700 --> 00:12:46,699
路易斯安那州立大學研究生 名列前茅
LSU grad, top of her class.

297
00:12:46,701 --> 00:12:48,434
說了吧 什麼都查不到
Like I said, squat.

298
00:12:48,436 --> 00:12:52,305
聽我說 我知道監聽Hamilton比什麼都重要
Look, I know the Hamilton wire is important and everything,

299
00:12:52,307 --> 00:12:54,574
但也許是時候讓Pride參與進來了
but think maybe it's time to loop Pride in?

300
00:12:54,576 --> 00:12:58,077
King希望我們能找到線索
King's expecting us to find leads.

301
00:13:00,081 --> 00:13:01,347
繼續調查吧
Let's keep digging.

302
00:13:01,349 --> 00:13:03,716
好吧
All right.

303
00:13:07,155 --> 00:13:08,654
嘿 大家好
Hey, guys.

304
00:13:08,656 --> 00:13:10,590
天啊 回到這裏看著你們在那邊
Oh, man, it's so weird being back here

305
00:13:10,592 --> 00:13:11,991
感覺好奇怪
and seeing you guys there.

306
00:13:11,993 --> 00:13:15,528
這種感覺就像是"我以為自己離開了 他們又把我拉回去..."
It's like, 「Just when I thought I was out, they pulled...」

307
00:13:11,993 --> 00:13:15,528
{\a6}原文：Just when I thought I was out,they pull me back in

308
00:13:15,530 --> 00:13:18,264
是《教父3》裏Michael Corleone的台詞
It's Michael Corleone, from, uh, from <i>The Godfather 3.</i>

309
00:13:20,902 --> 00:13:23,302
我的屏幕好像... 卡住了
Guys, I think my... my screen froze.

310
00:13:23,304 --> 00:13:24,904
說說被害者的彈道分析
Ballistics on the victim, please.

311
00:13:24,906 --> 00:13:26,238
對 好的
Right, sure.

312
00:13:26,240 --> 00:13:28,274
死者身上的彈道模式表明
Well, the bullet pattern on our dead Marine

313
00:13:28,276 --> 00:13:31,010
13發子彈全部來自於MP5衝鋒鎗
suggests that all 13 bullets came from an MP5.

314
00:13:31,012 --> 00:13:32,778
要我說 那真是槍林彈雨
Which, if you ask me, that's overkill.

315
00:13:32,780 --> 00:13:35,548
更有理由懷疑 是她的同夥殺了她
Even more reason to suspect her crew took her out.

316
00:13:35,550 --> 00:13:36,716
即使如此 還是有些地方對不上
Still, something doesn't add up.

317
00:13:36,718 --> 00:13:38,618
他們搶劫的時候用的是橡皮子彈
They went out of their way to use rubber bullets

318
00:13:38,620 --> 00:13:40,186
現在卻用真的子彈
for the heist, but then use real bullets

319
00:13:40,188 --> 00:13:41,420
去殺自己人嗎
to kill one of their own?

320
00:13:41,422 --> 00:13:44,023
或許他們知道 殺警察會被判處死刑
Maybe they knew killing cops guarantees the needle.

321
00:13:44,025 --> 00:13:47,059
但如果他們把其中一把槍變成了殺人兇器
Yeah, but if any of those guns end up as the murder weapon,

322
00:13:47,061 --> 00:13:48,327
他們還是會被判處死刑
they'll get the needle anyway.

323
00:13:48,329 --> 00:13:49,895
我們漏掉了什麼
We're missing something.

324
00:13:49,897 --> 00:13:51,931
嗨 那些橡膠子彈有什麼發現嗎
Hey, did you get anything on those rubber bullets yet?

325
00:13:53,034 --> 00:13:54,367
你們讓我驗屍完
You wanted me to call

326
00:13:54,369 --> 00:13:56,769
馬上給你們打電話
as soon as the autopsy was completed.

327
00:13:56,771 --> 00:13:58,170
哇 嘿 醫生
Whoa. Hey, Doc.

328
00:13:58,172 --> 00:14:00,106
簡直了 這就跟從前一樣
This is so crazy, it's like old times.

329
00:14:00,108 --> 00:14:01,874
你 我 血漿
You, me, plasmas.

330
00:14:01,876 --> 00:14:03,476
我不知道你在你的實驗室 Sebastian
I didn't know you were in your lab, Sebastian.

331
00:14:03,478 --> 00:14:05,011
你怎麼沒來打招呼呢
Why didn't you say something?

332
00:14:05,013 --> 00:14:06,912
我知道當你忙於解剖抽不開身的時候
Well, I know better than to bother you

333
00:14:06,914 --> 00:14:08,781
還是不要打擾你為好
when you're elbow deep in liver.

334
00:14:08,783 --> 00:14:10,116
抱歉打斷你們
I hate to interrupt.

335
00:14:10,118 --> 00:14:11,951
驗屍結果 對
Autopsy results, right.

336
00:14:11,953 --> 00:14:13,319
好吧 不出所料
Okay, no surprises.

337
00:14:13,321 --> 00:14:16,255
死因是多處槍傷
C.O.D.: multiple gunshot wounds.

338
00:14:16,257 --> 00:14:19,759
子彈擊中了每個重要的動脈和器官
The bullets hit every major artery and organ,

339
00:14:19,761 --> 00:14:21,560
擊中其中任何一個部位都足以致死
and any one of them would've sufficed.

340
00:14:21,562 --> 00:14:25,297
這顯然是一起聲明性的謀殺
This was obviously a statement killing.

341
00:14:25,299 --> 00:14:27,767
好讓其他成員乖乖聽話
One way to keep the rest of the crew in line.

342
00:14:27,769 --> 00:14:29,535
但是 有一個異常
However, there is an anomaly.

343
00:14:29,537 --> 00:14:32,071
在Bellacroix女士被殺之前
Before Ms. Bellacroix was murdered,

344
00:14:32,073 --> 00:14:34,840
有人縫合了她在搶劫時
someone sutured the initial gunshot wound

